<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870428-0102 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Conwest Exploration Co.</HL><DD> 04/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CEX.B </IN><TEXT>   CONWEST EXPLORATION CO., Toronto, said it sold $60 million (Canadian) of 7.25% debentures priced at par and due 2002 to three Canadian securities dealers. The securities are convertible at $18 of debentures for each Conwest Class B subordinated voting share until June 15, 1994, and at $19.50 of debentures a share thereafter. The oil, gas and mining concern said proceeds will be used for oil and gas acquisitions. In trading yesterday on the Toronto Stock Exchange, Conwest Class B closed at $15.375 a share, up 12.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>